Nollywood actress, Tonto Dikeh has asked that Chrisland school pays to take down the viral video of its female student involved in sexual activity. A video emerged on Monday showing some teenagers identified as students of the school filming adult content. Reactions have continued to trail the video, with many celebrities condemning the teens, the school and their parents. Tonto Dikeh in a post on Instagram, Tuesday, condemned those still sharing the video on social media. She disclosed that she reached out to someone that can take down the video from the internet but the price is outrageous. The actress offered to donate N500,000 and called on concerned parties, including Chrisland School to contribute to taking down the explicit content of its students from the internet. Her post read: “I have been in touch with someone who can get this video off the net for good! The price is outrageous, I will donate N500 thousand naria only and we can push this to concerned fans and children advocators to contribute or the parents can work it up! “Whichever way the first step is trying to heal these kids and work on how to punish the school for its involvement in the cover-up and neglect! “If we want to help, we can start from here! Chrisland school can also Pay it off, that’s the least they can do now. “Yes it may be on people’s phones but you cannot Google it and may not be able to upload ever again without alerting the authorities once posted again.”